DUTSE – The Expanding Social Protection for Inclusive Development a project implemented by Action Against Hunger, and Save the Children International with funding by the UK government through foreign CommonWealth and Development Office, (FCDO) Supported Quarterly meeting for Jigawa State Media Platforms. Speaking in his capacity as ESPID representative at the Quarterly Meeting of Jigawa State Media Platform on Social Protection Action Against Hunger Advocacy and Communication Officer, Malam Umar Ibrahim Umar, has on behalf of ESPID extend its profound appreciations to the Jigawa State government for continued implementing and supporting social protection activities for the betterment of its citizen, especially poor and vulnerable across the state. In his welcome address, the Media Chairman of the platform, Comrade Mikhail Tsoho, called for positive contributions among members in achieving the desired objectives in line with ESPID mandate of creating awareness on inclusive social protection.